{"id":14881814,"mediaExerciseId":"1d9d8c6d-d5ea-4663-b822-64cb730a88c7","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"23.4","sectionTitle":"Hedging with Futures Contracts","pageNumber":776,"solutions":[{"id":5990268,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This question deals with the concept of hedging using futures contracts and cross-hedging to alter a company's risk profile. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**4a.** The primary difference between the futures contract and a forward contract is how they take note of the gains and losses.\n\nIn a **forward contract** the gains/losses are recorded at the end of the agreement or on the purchase date. This means that the price during that period is the only indicator.\n\nOn the other hand, a **futures contract** measures the gains and losses incurred **daily** until the end of the contract. \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":256,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/b33707123200e481f2b68154b3840499/35b02f4dcebd8e85bde9d6ad46970d4b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/b33707123200e481f2b68154b3840499/35b02f4dcebd8e85bde9d6ad46970d4b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**4b.** **Cross-hedging** is the process of leveraging your current asset to a different but related asset in order to offset possible losses. This can be done instead of a futures contract if ever a futures contract is not available or not viable for the chosen asset. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/b33707123200e481f2b68154b3840499/8c9d79c5e42b726284031a42ed104067/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/b33707123200e481f2b68154b3840499/8c9d79c5e42b726284031a42ed104067/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"dd862f6a-f373-480d-ba5c-8828696f4a25","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881815,"exerciseName":"5","page":778,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"01370cbe-1cf7-4719-8162-4be94edfe8dc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-exercises-5-01370cbe-1cf7-4719-8162-4be94edfe8dc"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881813,"exerciseName":"3","page":772,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1ff718b4-b720-4217-85a3-1fa5aa4b78d7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-exercises-3-1ff718b4-b720-4217-85a3-1fa5aa4b78d7"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-exercises-4-1d9d8c6d-d5ea-4663-b822-64cb730a88c7"}